  "title": "Quality Engineer (NPI) - WCAN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support New Product Introduction (NPI) by managing product quality from testing and sample builds through to mass production.</li>\n  <li>Conduct First Article Inspections (FAI) and compile data into detailed First Article Inspection Reports (FAIR).</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with program managers on NPI builds and engineering assessments.</li>\n  <li>Train QC inspectors prior to handing over NPI projects to production.</li>\n  <li>Perform qualification and validation of equipment, processes, and test methods.</li>\n  <li>Develop, review, and update Work Instructions, PFMEA, Control Plans, Quality Standards, and sample boards for production transfer.</li>\n  <li>Partner with engineering on jig design, including reviewing 2D drawings, identifying issues, and assessing jig requirements.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Holds at least a Diploma in Precision, Mechanical, Manufacturing Engineering, Quality Management, or a related engineering field.</li>\n  <li>One year of experience in Quality Engineering or Manufacturing is advantageous</li>\n  <li>Skilled in applying quality methodologies including SPC, PFMEA, Control Plans, CPK, GR&amp;R, and using Minitab software.</li>\n  <li>Competent in interpreting engineering drawings, with a solid understanding of Geometrical Dimensioning &amp; Tolerancing (GD&amp;T).</li>\n  <li>Effective at organizing workloads, juggling multiple priorities, and managing time efficiently.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication skills, both spoken and written, paired with good interpersonal abilities.</li>\n  <li>Self-motivated, disciplined, and takes initiative.</li>\n  <li>Collaborative team member with a dedication to responsibility and consistent performance.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel: Nyon Hock Sen (Aden)</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Reg No: R24124070</p>",
